Privacy Policy for Quiet Sudoku

Effective date: 16/03/2026
Developer: Joshua Lewis
Contact: cloudheavyindustries@proton.me

Quiet Sudoku respects your privacy. This app is designed to work primarily on your device and to minimise data handling.

1. Information We Collect

Quiet Sudoku does not collect, transmit, store, or share personal information from users during normal use of the app.

Specifically, Quiet Sudoku does not:
	•	require account creation or sign-in
	•	use advertising SDKs
	•	use analytics or tracking tools
	•	collect identifiers for advertising or cross-app tracking
	•	upload gameplay, statistics, or puzzle history to our servers
	•	maintain a server-hosted puzzle database tied to your use of the app

2. How the App Works

Quiet Sudoku is designed to function offline by default. Puzzle generation and gameplay occur on your device.

App settings, game progress, and statistics are stored locally on your device. Where supported by the operating system, this local data may be protected using the device’s built-in security features, such as iOS file protection.

3. Network Use

Quiet Sudoku does not make outbound network connections during normal gameplay.

Any backup, export, or sharing action is initiated by you through system-provided sharing or export features. When you choose to export or share data, that action is controlled by you and handled through the operating system or the destination you select.

4. App Store Privacy Labels

Based on the current version of Quiet Sudoku:
	•	Data Linked to You: None
	•	Data Used to Track You: None
	•	Data Not Linked to You: None

If the app’s features change in the future, these disclosures and this Privacy Policy will be updated accordingly.

5. Third-Party Services

Quiet Sudoku does not include third-party advertising, analytics, or tracking SDKs in the current version of the app.

If a future version adds any third-party service that collects or processes data, this Privacy Policy will be updated before or when that change is released.

6. Children’s Privacy

Quiet Sudoku does not knowingly collect personal information from children or from any users.

7. Data Retention

Because Quiet Sudoku does not collect personal data on our servers, we do not retain personal information remotely.

Data stored locally on your device remains there unless you delete the app, remove the data, or choose to export it yourself.

8. Your Choices

Because Quiet Sudoku does not collect personal data during normal use, there is generally no account data for you to access, correct, or delete on our servers.

You can manage local app data directly on your device, including by deleting the app and its local data, subject to how your operating system manages app storage and backups.

9. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect app changes, legal requirements, or App Store disclosure updates. The updated version will be posted at the privacy policy URL associated with the app and will show the revised effective date.

